third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis is rooting for Cody Wood, noting that many respected guys are behind him, but acknowledges Joseph's strength.

Cody Wood.strength: Strong, especially with pull-ups, but relatively new to the sport.

Joseph Meranto.strength: Strong, impressed with his win over Kevin Palco.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis is rooting for Hunter Noffz, believing he has the potential to become a superstar.

Hunter Noffz.strength: Has the fire and electric potential to become a superstar.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis believes Mindaugas will beat Janis, comparing their rivalry to Todd Hutchings and John Brzenk.

Mindaugas Tarasaitis.strength: Superstar, has leveled up since his last match with Justin.
Mindaugas Tarasaitis.previous_match_summary: Beat Justin in a close match.

Janis Amolins.strength: Strong, but Travis thinks Mindaugas has surpassed him.
Janis Amolins.previous_match_summary: Almost lost to Justin but came back.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis thinks Dave is the underdog but has a chance if he can keep his hand strong early.
third_party_predictions.style_conflict: Dave needs to avoid letting Georgi control the hand and wrist early.

Georgi Tsvetkov.strength: Great hand and wrist positioning, good endurance.
Georgi Tsvetkov.previous_match_summary: Had great hand control against Devon.

Dave Chaffee.strength: Strong side pressure, but hand may open up over time.
Dave Chaffee.previous_match_summary: Needs to avoid early hand fatigue.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis thinks Devon is too strong and Corey won't be able to beat him three times.
third_party_predictions.style_conflict: Corey needs to keep the lane closed and avoid Devon's manipulations.

Devon Larratt.strength: Unbelievable strength, especially in controlling matches.

Corey West.strength: Good but not at the highest level.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis thinks Yoshi will win, especially if John can't pin him early.
third_party_predictions.style_conflict: John needs to avoid a prolonged war with Yoshi.

Yoshinobu Kanai.previous_match_summary: Pulled Todd better than Irakli did.

John Brzenk.strength: Still strong but may not be as dominant as before.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis thinks Ongarbaev could dominate but acknowledges Matt's recent improvements.

Matt Mask.strength: Improved after stem cell treatment, strong recent performances.
Matt Mask.health: Had elbow surgery, now recovering well.

Kydyrgali Ongarbaev.strength: Former pound-for-pound contender, still very strong.
Kydyrgali Ongarbaev.previous_match_summary: Lost to Tata Shinks and Petrenko post-surgery.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis thinks Prudnik is better than recent showings and could win if he's in form.
third_party_predictions.style_conflict: Cody needs to fire off early to have a chance.

Evgeny Prudnik.strength: Can be dangerous if in form.
Evgeny Prudnik.previous_match_summary: Had wins over strong opponents in the past.

Kody Merritt.strength: Strong, but needs to exploit Prudnik's weaknesses.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Travis thinks John Therrien is strong and could give Craig a tough match.

John Therrien.previous_match_summary: Beat a strong left-handed opponent recently.

third_party_predictions.prediction_summary: Engin thinks it will be tough for Sharkevich but acknowledges his strength.

Andrei Sharkevich.previous_match_summary: Has put in a lot of work.
